eted presentation. I\'m planning to replace the current \"Content & Marketing\" card with a focused bulleted list, and I\'m debating the layout, potentially using a three-column arrangement to best display skills. The \"Professional Skills\" section will now feature UX/UI & AI, Content & Digital Marketing, and General Tools & Tech.\n\n\n**Refining Skill Categorization**\n\nI\'m now revising the layout to accommodate all skills logically. I\'ve decided on a three-card structure using a grid layout to create three columns: \"UX, UI & Tech\" will display progress bars for the newer skills; \"Content & Marketing\" will present the bullets; and \"Tools & General Skills\" will present the bulleted older skills. I am thinking a grid layout like `grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` will be the best choice.\n\n\n**Adjusting Display Columns**\n\nI\'m now refining the visual presentation, modifying the column structure to better utilize screen space. I\'m focusing on a `grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6` layout, which should improve the display. Card 2 will now contain the bullet points: Product Content Writing, product descriptions, SEO, and infographic skills. Additionally, I\'m introducing a Card 3, spanning full width, to showcase tools and technical capabilities using a unified bullet list.\n\n\n**Finalizing Content Arrangement**\n\nI\'m now implementing the bulleted lists within the resume structure. \"Content & Marketing\" will use bullet points to showcase skills in that domain. I\'m focusing on the \"Content & Marketing\" card, ensuring the list includes each element requested. Specifically, the \"Content & Marketing\" card will feature detailed bullet points, precisely addressing proficiency in product content writing, product descriptions, SEO, and infographic skills.\n\n\n**Implementing Bullet Points**\n\nI\'m now integrating the finalized bullet points into the updated UI structure, focusing on the content and structure of the \"Content & Marketing\" card. I\'ve re-examin