  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Redesigning the Portfolio**\n\nI\'m currently focused on transforming the resume portfolio site. My aim is to elevate its presentation to resemble a professional company or agency website. I\'m drawing inspiration from the linked Wix template, envisioning a sleek, modern, sectioned, and scrolling portfolio design.\n\n\n**Restructuring the Layout**\n\nI\'m now completely restructuring `App.tsx`. The goal is a landing-page-style portfolio, inspired by that Wix template. I\'m planning bold sections for the hero, about, skills, experience, portfolio, and contact info, all accessible via a sticky navbar. Details for the new sections will follow as I outline them. I\'m focusing on the user\'s name and details for the experience section.\n\n\n**Defining the Structure**\n\nI\'m now outlining key sections, including navbar, hero, and skills, for `App.tsx`. The goal is a clean, modern design. I\'m prioritizing large typography and considering a light/dark minimal theme with alternating section backgrounds, potentially using `bg-slate-900` for the hero. I\'m also planning to use `framer-motion` for entrance animations; I\'ve confirmed that `motion` is installed and ready to be imported from `motion/react`. I\'m starting the `App.tsx` rewrite.\n\n\n**Organizing the Content**\n\nI\'ve got the portfolio content organized now, starting with sections for Experience, Portfolio projects, Education & Certifications, and a Contact Footer. I\'m focusing on defining the structure with constants for the experience content, including a role, company, period, description, and responsibilities. I\'m aiming for a professional timeline appearance, to present it in a visually engaging and informative way.\n\n\n**Refining the Details**\n\nI\'m now integrating detailed experience data, like roles, periods, and responsibilities, into a structured format. I\'m building constant data structures to hold this info, and I\'m currently focused on visually appealing timeline presentation. The goal is clarity and readability. I\'m also organizing skills content into categories now.\n\n\n**Styling the Portfolio**\n\nI\'m now diving into the styling, aiming for that agency-website vibe. I\'m focusing on large fonts, high contrast, and padding for a sleek look. I\'m checking the `motion` package import; it\'s `motion/react`, as I suspected. I\'m drafting `App.tsx` now with `lucide-react` icons. The goal is the clean, professional feel of a company website.\n\n\n**Implementing the Core Structure**\n\nI\'m now implementing the core single-page structure. I\'m focusing on that elegant agency look, with a fixed navigation bar for smooth scrolling, and large imagery and type. I\'m aiming for sections: hero, expertise, and more. The hero will be dark with white text, and the expertise section will be lighter, creating contrast. I\'m also implementing a `mix-blend-difference` effect on the navigation.\n\n\n**Refining the Theme**\n\nI\'ve decided to refine the theme now. I\'m focusing on a polished light/dark mode and great typography. I\'m considering Space Grotesk for headings and Inter for body text, but a standard Tailwind font with `tracking-tight` might do. I\'m now drafting the navigation component, considering a solid or glass effect, rather than the buggy `mix-blend-difference`.\n\n```tsx\n<div className=\"font-sans text-slate-900 antialiased bg-white selection:bg-slate-900 selection:text-white\">\n\n```\n\nI\'m structuring the core sections very cleanly, too.\n\n\n**Designing the Navigation**\n\nI\'m now focused on the navigation bar, building the top-level structure. I\'m aiming for clean aesthetic with smooth scroll links to each section, and am considering a solid or glass effect with Tailwind CSS. I\'m also considering a light/dark mode switch, which may be implemented after all other components. I\'m incorporating a \"Get in touch\" button. I\'ve drafted the component with the core links.\n\n\n**Refining the Hero Section**\n\nI\'m now revising the hero section for impact. I\'ve got a headline \"Crafting content & digital experiences,\" with gradients and animations. My description is now more concise, highlighting my Product Content, UX/UI, and AI expertise. I\'m focusing on clarity and visual appeal for the hero. I\'m aiming for a compelling first impression.\n\n\n\n**Updating the Expertise**\n\nI\'ve got the expertise section mapped out now, and I\'m adding more specific details. I\'m focusing on \"Product Content & Marketing\", \"UX/UI & Analytics\", and \"AI & Engineering\" categories. Each has sub-bullets describing my expertise, which include things like writing product descriptions and UX design for seamless user experiences. The aim is to create a clear section, that explains my skillsets.\n\n\n**Revising Experience Presentation**\n\nI\'m now revising the experience section\'s layout, preferring a modern grid of large cards as the best visual presentation of past experience. I\'m focusing on incorporating the Wix template\'s half/half image-text split with whitespace. I\'m also considering abstract imagery and typography with soft colors to enhance the presentation. The goal is clean and modern.\n\n\n**Refining the Color Scheme**\n\nI\'m now implementing the color scheme from the Wix template, aiming for a professional feel. I\'m focusing on `bg-zinc-50`, `text-zinc-900`, and an accent color of `orange-600` or `indigo-600`. The goal is to emulate the template\'s structured and bold look, with a company agency vibe. I\'m starting to rewrite `App.tsx` with this in mind, and also integrating a CV/Resume portfolio look.\n\n\n**Integrating Experience Data**\n\nI\'m now integrating detailed work experience data. I\'m focusing on \"Product Content & Department Manager\" at B2S, and \"Digital Content Writer\" at Home Product Center. I\'m structuring these as card-like entries in a grid. I\'ve built the data constants, including the responsibilities as detailed bullets. I\'m aiming for an appealing, informative display, highlighting the key roles and responsibilities.\n\n\n**Adding the New Data**\n\nI\'m now integrating education, certificates, and personal information to expand the portfolio\'s completeness. I\'m focusing on crafting concise displays for education and certifications, and the personal info is ready for concise inclusion. I\'ll need to update my age, though. I\'m aiming for clarity in these additions.\n\n\n\n**Enhancing the Aesthetic**\n\nI\'m now really improving the hero. I\'m focusing on that big text and dark background for the first impression. I\'m adding subtle blurs, which are really making the design pop. I\'m getting a good feeling with this design, and how it will improve. It\'s really beginning to look professional.\n\n\n**Refining the Sections**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the sections, ensuring a professional agency look. I\'m moving toward a bright white \"About\" section after the dark hero. I\'m planning a grid layout for expertise and education, and a list/timeline for experience. The goal is to provide a comprehensive, streamlined portfolio. The contact section will finalize it. I\'m focusing on aesthetics.\n\n\n**Refactoring the Tool Call**\n\nI\'m now changing the approach for file edits. Instead of attempting `edit_file`, I\'ll use `multi_edit_file`, and this simplifies the approach. I want to replace the whole `src/App.tsx`, and I\'m ready to write the new data for inclusion. The work on this front is going quite well.\n\n\n"
