  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing App.tsx**\n\nI\'m now fully committed to overwriting `App.tsx` with a completely new structure, now that I have all necessary context. My goal is to craft a polished, creative agency-style site using `framer-motion` to handle subtle animations and reveals. I\'ll make sure it looks great!\n\n\n**Adding Premium Effects**\n\nI\'m now integrating subtle animations for a premium feel, inspired by Wix templates. I\'ve started building the `App.tsx` file with `framer-motion`, and I am working on the initial structure with a `SectionHeading` component. Next, I\'ll flesh out each section with components. I\'m focusing on ensuring it looks and feels great!\n\n\n**Implementing Scroll Effect**\n\nI\'ve implemented a scroll effect to change the navigation bar\'s appearance. It uses a state variable, `isScrolled`, that updates based on the window\'s scroll position. I added a `useEffect` hook to handle the scroll event listener, making it active when scrolling the page. Now the navigation becomes visible upon scrolling.\n\n\n**Refining Navigation Integration**\n\nI\'ve just added scroll effects to refine the navigation bar\'s behavior. I implemented a state variable called `isScrolled`, which changes according to the window\'s scroll position, and a `useEffect` hook handles the scroll event listener. Now, the navigation dynamically adapts its appearance upon scrolling. The styling works well, and the effect is quite subtle!\n\n\n**Designing Hero Section**\n\n\\n\\nI\'m now fully immersed in designing the hero section. I\'m focusing on text and animation, using `motion.div` for initial opacity and `y` position, and I\'ve set a `transition` to control the animation duration and easing. The goal is to make a dynamic introduction, including the name and a concise description below. The animation will be subtle, but effective.\n\n\n**Designing About Section**\n\nI am now designing the profile overview (About) section. I\'m focusing on crafting a concise and impactful \"Profile Info\" section. I\'m implementing a text section with a simple \"ArrowDownRight\" icon for navigation. The section is now set up and ready for styling and content.\n\n\n**Adding Contact Details**\n\nI\'ve just added contact details, including DOB, phone numbers, email, and location. I added these contact details as a list. I\'ve placed this in a formatted section, and styled it to complement the existing design and also used a tracking space between letters for a better look. This section is structured for clarity.\n\n\n**Defining Expertise**\n\nI am now structuring the \"Expertise\" section, drawing upon my core attributes: I see myself as flexible, ambitious, and deeply committed to continuous learning. I\'m focusing on weaving these qualities into a compelling presentation of my skill set, highlighting \'Communication,\' \'Teamwork,\' \'Enthusiasm,\' and other relevant skills. I\'ll make sure to convey my enthusiasm for building digital products.\n\n\n**Defining Expertise**\n\nI\'m structuring the \"Expertise\" section using a grid layout to showcase skills with `ExpertiseCard` components, including \"Content & Marketing\" and \"UX/UI & Layouts.\" Each card lists relevant skills with icons for visual appeal. I\'m focusing on concisely presenting my diverse expertise using a grid structure.\n\n\n**Adding Office Skills**\n\nI\'ve just added expertise cards for MS Office skills in a skills grid. This includes proficiency in cross-platform environments. This section neatly presents my ability to work efficiently across various platforms and tools within the office suite.\n\n\n**Describing My Experience**\n\nI\'m now detailing my professional experience with an `ExperienceRow` component. I\'m focusing on concisely presenting my role at B2S (Central Retail) - Central Group. I am adding a descriptive narrative of my responsibilities, incorporating specific achievements like UX/UI design and AI-driven projects.\n\n\n**Describing My Content**\n\nI am now focusing on refining my content and adding it to `ExperienceRow` components. I\'ve added my role at Home Product Center Pub Co., Ltd. and a description of my achievements and activities, including writing product descriptions and digital articles to drive engagement while overseeing online marketing campaigns. I am focused on creating compelling, engaging content.\n\n\n**Adding Education Information**\n\nI\'m now detailing my educational background using a structured layout. I\'m focusing on concisely presenting my degree from Ramkhamhaeng University, including dates, the degree, and relevant majors and minors. This will provide a clear snapshot of my academic foundation.\n\n\n**Listing Certifications**\n\nI\'m now detailing my certifications, structuring them with dates and descriptions, and focusing on a concise format for clarity. I\'m adding an \"Infographic Design\" certification from Srinakharinwirot University (Thai-MOOC) from Feb 2020, and a \"Creative Marketing\" certification from June 2020. I\'m building a simple layout for it.\n\n\n**Finalizing Educational Overview**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on my educational overview, including education from Ming Chuan University and the National Open University. I\'m making sure all the education details are clear, concise, and effectively presented in the section. This wraps up the details of the educational background section.\n\n\n**Refining Footer Section**\n\nI\'m now refining the footer, focusing on contact details and copyright information. I added my email and phone number, styled for readability. Also, I updated the copyright notice. I\'ve designed the footer to be professional and informative.\n\n\n**Structuring Expertise Content**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the content within my existing expertise sections. I am working through the design phase and content, including using a grid layout to make sure my abilities are displayed in a clean way. I\'m leveraging the `ExpertiseCard` component to showcase skills like \"Technical Skills.\"\n\n\n**Adding Experience Detail**\n\nI\'m now detailing an `ExperienceRow` component, which will be added to the experience section. I\'ve designed the component to have a structure for roles, dates, and experience descriptions. I\'m focusing on crafting a concise and visually appealing display of my work history. I\'ll make sure it\'s clear and well-organized.\n\n\n**Updating Experience Design**\n\nI\'m now revising the design and content within my experience section. I\'ve updated the `ExperienceRow` component with a new structure to include a clear division of roles, dates, and experience descriptions, along with a fix for the latest `framer-motion` v12. I\'m focusing on improved readability, and a more visually appealing display of my work history.\n\n\n"
