  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Implementing Mobile Navigation**\n\nI\'ve been working on the mobile navigation. The current focus is implementing a hamburger menu icon on the nav bar for smaller screens. I\'m also managing a state variable to track whether the mobile menu is open or closed, which will inform the rendering of either a full-screen or slide-out menu.\n\n\n**Refining Mobile Menu Logic**\n\nI\'ve implemented the mobile menu rendering with conditional logic based on `isMobileMenuOpen`. I\'m now integrating `lucide-react` icons for the Menu and X icons, and handling the menu closing upon link clicks. Currently, I\'m working with the state and conditional rendering using the provided code.\n\n\n**Finalizing Mobile Menu**\n\nI\'ve just added the ability to click the close icon (X) to hide the menu, and have added click handlers on the menu links themselves to also close the menu. I\'ve also incorporated the `lucide-react` X icon as planned. The menu functions as intended!\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 979602812
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
